tributions of others, many of them women, whose names are far less known. At the end of the complex, exciting, and at times dismaying chronicle, it is likely that readers will never again watch Hollywood films without thinking about the roles of makeup and hairdressing in creating both fictional characters and stars as emblems of an idealized and undeniably mesmerizing visual perfection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aBeauty operatorszCaliforniazLos AngelesvBiography. 0aFilm hairstyling. 0aFilm makeup. 0aMakeup artistszCaliforniazLos AngelesvBiography. 0aMotion picturesxProduction and directionzCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictureszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistory. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  abeauty, makeup, beauty standards, hair, hairdressing, Hollywood, film, television, T.V., fame, celebrity, cosmetics, makeup artists, hairdresser, gender, silent film, media, studio, studio era, studio film era, cosmetology, history, flawless, image.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076647940uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9780813563602?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813563602423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813563602/original  a978-3-11-076647-9  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK